01:06:00,520 --> 01:06:03,671
Pull out of it.
All right, everyone. Look alive.

884
01:06:05,800 --> 01:06:10,555
Mr Mullen, we're gonna
get you set up right over here.
We'll get you wired up with a mike.

885
01:06:10,680 --> 01:06:14,150
I will signal to you
from next to the camera.

886
01:06:14,280 --> 01:06:17,033
Ready to go? On five, four...

887
01:06:17,160 --> 01:06:19,879
three, two--

888
01:06:20,000 --> 01:06:24,073
Good afternoon.
We are interrupting this programme
to bring you an exclusive report.

889
01:06:24,200 --> 01:06:28,318
As you know, we've been
following the Mullen kidnapping
for about a day or so.

890
01:06:28,440 --> 01:06:31,432
We will get back to
our regular programme, but right now
we're going to show you something...

891
01:06:31,560 --> 01:06:33,630
that you will only see
right here--

892
01:06:33,760 --> 01:06:36,115
Tom Mullen,
Sean Mullen's father.

893
01:06:36,240 --> 01:06:38,959
Mr Mullen?

894
01:06:43,080 --> 01:06:44,877
Tom, you're on.

895
01:06:47,360 --> 01:06:49,112
The whole world now knows...

896
01:06:49,240 --> 01:06:51,549
my son, Sean Mullen, was kidnapped...

897
01:06:51,680 --> 01:06:53,796
for ransom three days ago.

898
01:06:53,920 --> 01:06:56,480
This is a recent
photograph of him.

899
01:06:56,600 --> 01:06:59,592
Sean, if you're watching,
we love you.

900
01:07:00,920 --> 01:07:02,478
And this--

901
01:07:02,600 --> 01:07:05,273
Well, this is what waits
for the man that took him.

902
01:07:05,400 --> 01:07:07,231
This is your ransom.

903
01:07:07,360 --> 01:07:09,191
Wait. Shh, shh.
I want to see this.

904
01:07:09,320 --> 01:07:11,754
Two million dollars
in unmarked bills, just like you wanted.

905
01:07:11,880 --> 01:07:15,998
- Oh-ho!
- But this is as close
as you'll ever get to it.

906
01:07:16,120 --> 01:07:19,192
You'll never see one dollar
of this money...

907
01:07:19,320 --> 01:07:22,949
because no ransom will ever
be paid for my son.

908
01:07:23,080 --> 01:07:25,799
Not one dime. Not one penny.

909
01:07:25,920 --> 01:07:30,072
Instead, I'm offering this money
as a reward on your head.

910
01:07:31,480 --> 01:07:34,438
Dead or alive.
It doesn't matter.

911
01:07:34,560 --> 01:07:37,791
So congratulations. You've just
become a $2 million lottery ticket.

912
01:07:37,920 --> 01:07:41,196
Except the odds
are much, much better.

913
01:07:41,320 --> 01:07:44,312
Do you know anyone that wouldn't
turn you in for $2 million?

914
01:07:44,440 --> 01:07:47,591
I don't think you do.
I doubt it.

915
01:07:47,720 --> 01:07:51,918
So wherever you go and whatever you do,
this money will be tracking you
down for all time.

916
01:07:52,040 --> 01:07:55,191
And to ensure that it does,
to keep interest alive...

917
01:07:55,320 --> 01:07:59,359
I'm running a full-page ad
in every major newspaper every Sunday...

918
01:07:59,480 --> 01:08:01,357
for as long as it takes.

919
01:08:01,480 --> 01:08:05,598
But-- and this is
your last chance--

920
01:08:05,720 --> 01:08:09,679
if you return my son
alive, uninjured...

921
01:08:09,800 --> 01:08:11,438
I'll withdraw the bounty.

922
01:08:11,560 --> 01:08:14,996
With any luck,
you can simply disappear.

923
01:08:15,120 --> 01:08:20,194
Understand-- you will never see
this money. Not one dollar.

924
01:08:21,640 --> 01:08:23,710
So you still have a chance
to do the right thing.

925
01:08:26,240 --> 01:08:30,153
If you don't, well, then God
be with you because nobody else
on this Earth will be.

926
01:08:30,280 --> 01:08:32,555
Well, he's got nerve.

927
01:08:36,040 --> 01:08:39,396
That's it.

928
01:08:39,520 --> 01:08:41,795
Well, there you have it, Rosanna.
A shocking turn of events.

929
01:08:41,920 --> 01:08:44,309
The ransom has turned
into a $2-million bounty.

930
01:08:44,440 --> 01:08:46,795
Tony, it's obviously
a very dangerous situation.

931
01:08:46,920 --> 01:08:49,673
Anything could happen. Of course,
we wish him the best of luck.

932
01:08:49,800 --> 01:08:54,191
Did you notice he,
uh, described the kidnapper
as a $2 million lottery ticket?

933
01:08:54,320 --> 01:08:56,834
- The stakes are high on this one.
- Yeah, as you mentioned also--

934
01:09:01,480 --> 01:09:04,153
- Could you turn it off?
Could you turn it off?
- Mr Mullen also appealed to his son.

935
01:09:04,280 --> 01:09:06,748
He said, "Sean, if you're
out there listening, I love you."

936
01:09:06,880 --> 01:09:09,519
- It was very heartbreaking.
- Also, our producer is telling me, uh--

937
01:09:11,480 --> 01:09:14,631
- Yeah.
- Mullen, you're a fool!

938
01:09:14,760 --> 01:09:16,557
Stupid ass!

939
01:09:19,400 --> 01:09:21,391
I'm proud of you!

940
01:09:23,280 --> 01:09:26,078
A pair of armed bandits
held 'em up last night.

941
01:09:26,200 --> 01:09:30,273
Police say a pair of gun-toting crooks
went into the Korean church
at Murray Street...

942
01:09:30,400 --> 01:09:32,391
in Flushing last night
and announced a robbery.

943
01:09:32,520 --> 01:09:35,159
- They took wallets, handbags--
- Hey, where'd they take the kid?

944
01:09:35,280 --> 01:09:37,475
You know. The place we said.

945
01:09:42,000 --> 01:09:43,672
I had to do this.

946
01:09:43,800 --> 01:09:45,950
You had to do this?

947
01:09:48,880 --> 01:09:51,678
You had to do this?

948
01:09:51,800 --> 01:09:54,678
Kate, please.

949
01:09:54,800 --> 01:09:58,509
I'm so scared, but I know if
I give him the money, he'll kill Sean.

950
01:09:58,640 --> 01:10:01,154
- I would if I was him.
- What did you just say?

951
01:10:01,280 --> 01:10:03,236
Just look at it
from his point of view.

952
01:10:03,360 --> 01:10:05,999
You think you're smart.
You've got everybody off balance.

953
01:10:06,120 --> 01:10:08,714
- You think you've
got it all figured out.
- You tryin' to screw me?

954
01:10:08,840 --> 01:10:12,150
And then suddenly,
out of left field, the one thing
you thought would never happen does.

955
01:10:12,280 --> 01:10:14,111
- We gotta end this.
- What are you doin'?

956
01:10:14,240 --> 01:10:17,198
No ransom, no money, no profit.
Nothing. Nothing but downside.

957
01:10:17,320 --> 01:10:22,235
Because you've got this boy's father--
he's coming on like a stark,
raving mad lunatic.

958
01:10:22,360 --> 01:10:25,796
- You turned her around, didn't you?
- I mean, the guy can piss $2 million...

959
01:10:25,920 --> 01:10:28,036
- but he's willing to risk everything
just to fuck you up.
- Don't!

960
01:10:28,160 --> 01:10:30,958
How can you negotiate with
a lunatic like that, huh? You can't.

961
01:10:31,080 --> 01:10:33,992
- Now you're off balance.
- Get down. Lay down!

962
01:10:34,120 --> 01:10:37,192
You wanna stay down there forever,
maggot? Did I get my money?

963
01:10:37,320 --> 01:10:40,676
Pretty soon you realize if you don't
return this kid in mint condition
as soon as possible...

964
01:10:40,800 --> 01:10:43,155
you're gonna be the most hunted man
on the face of the Earth.

965
01:10:43,280 --> 01:10:47,432
And this maniac will never,
ever quit until he's got you.

966
01:10:47,560 --> 01:10:50,597
Nobody pulls out on me.

967
01:10:50,720 --> 01:10:53,188
You know me.

968
01:10:53,320 --> 01:10:56,232
This is my show.
I say when it's over.

969
01:10:56,360 --> 01:10:58,635
- Take it back.
- No.
- Tell him that you were wrong.

970
01:10:58,760 --> 01:11:00,830
- Kate, no, I can't. No, Kate,
there is no other way. None.
- Take it back.

971
01:11:00,960 --> 01:11:04,077
- He's my son too,
and I want you to pay him.
- Kate. They will kill him.

972
01:11:04,200 --> 01:11:06,316
Please, all we have
is each other.

973
01:11:06,440 --> 01:11:10,638
Do you think any of them--
Do you think they give-- It's just us.

974
01:11:10,760 --> 01:11:13,035
Do you think I don't
want him back? ls that it?

975
01:11:13,160 --> 01:11:15,515
You think I wouldn't do absolutely
everything in my power to get him back?

976
01:11:15,640 --> 01:11:20,395
I'd cut my arm off.
I'd-- I want him back so bad.

977
01:11:20,520 --> 01:11:23,990
Katie, please. I don't think
I can take this if you're not with me.

978
01:11:38,920 --> 01:11:40,717
Don't quit on me.

979
01:11:51,840 --> 01:11:54,718
Tom. Now--

980
01:11:58,040 --> 01:12:00,793
I think what you did was wrong.

981
01:12:00,920 --> 01:12:03,593
You put your son at greater risk.

982
01:12:03,720 --> 01:12:06,553
Now, I need you
to withdraw that reward.

983
01:12:06,680 --> 01:12:09,319
Just pay this bastard.

984
01:12:09,440 --> 01:12:13,035
Now, I believe that
you will get your son back.

985
01:12:13,160 --> 01:12:17,039
And when we do,
we will nail this son of a bitch.

986
01:12:18,520 --> 01:12:21,990
Now, God forbid you don't...

987
01:12:22,120 --> 01:12:23,917
your son--

988
01:12:24,040 --> 01:12:26,952
I swear to you
I will work on nothing else.

989
01:12:27,080 --> 01:12:29,355
If I have to, I will take
a leave of absence from the FBl...

990
01:12:29,480 --> 01:12:31,994
and you can hire me as
your personal security consultant.

991
01:12:32,120 --> 01:12:34,953
And I will work on this
as long as I am physically able.

992
01:12:35,080 --> 01:12:36,877
- Lonnie, please. I--
- Tom.

993
01:12:37,000 --> 01:12:39,434
I never told anybody,
any of my people...

994
01:12:39,560 --> 01:12:43,758
about you and Jackie Brown, the real
truth of it, and maybe I never will.

995
01:12:46,320 --> 01:12:48,880
You think I'm worried
about going to jail?

996
01:12:53,880 --> 01:12:57,111
Mayor Barresi today voiced his
disapproval of Tom Mullen's decision.

997
01:12:57,240 --> 01:13:00,277
- Donna Hanover joins us
later in the broadcast.
- You, uh, care for an update?

998
01:13:00,400 --> 01:13:02,516
Oh, yeah.

999
01:13:02,640 --> 01:13:07,077
Well, in the last two hours
since your husband's TV thing,
we've had 4,000 calls.

1000
01:13:07,200 --> 01:13:11,716
- And you know how
many real, good, solid leads?
- How many?

1001
01:13:11,840 --> 01:13:15,389
Zero. And every time
one of these...

1002
01:13:15,520 --> 01:13:18,830
greedy little whack jobs calls...

1003
01:13:18,960 --> 01:13:22,191
that is one less agent
looking for your child.

1004
01:13:22,320 --> 01:13:24,550
Now, I gotta tell you, Kate.

1005
01:13:24,680 --> 01:13:29,674
I have never been confronted with such
an unbelievable act of sabotage...

1006
01:13:29,800 --> 01:13:31,711
by a parent toward
the recovery of their child...

1007
01:13:31,840 --> 01:13:33,831
as what your husband
pulled off here today.

1008
01:13:33,960 --> 01:13:38,795
It is all on you now to talk to your
husband, get him to withdraw this money.

1009
01:13:38,920 --> 01:13:41,514
- Otherwise we are in deep trouble.
- Withdraw the mo-- What if he's right?

1010
01:13:41,640 --> 01:13:46,031
What if they have no intention
of returning Sean at all?

1011
01:13:46,160 --> 01:13:48,879
- I trust him.
- You trust him?

1012
01:13:49,000 --> 01:13:52,197
Yeah. I believe in him.

1013
01:13:52,320 --> 01:13:54,959
I stick with Tom...

1014
01:13:55,080 --> 01:13:57,674
and we always manage
to land on high ground.

1015
01:13:58,760 --> 01:14:01,672
High ground? Huh.

1016
01:14:03,600 --> 01:14:06,751
Like with the Jackie Brown situation?

1017
01:14:08,320 --> 01:14:10,311
Yeah.

1018
01:14:14,640 --> 01:14:18,315
What exactly did
your husband tell you...

1019
01:14:18,440 --> 01:14:20,556
about Jackie Brown?

1020
01:14:28,480 --> 01:14:30,118
- David?
- Yeah.

1021
01:14:30,240 --> 01:14:32,913
- Can I talk to you for a minute?
- Yeah, sure.

1022
01:14:33,040 --> 01:14:37,033
Look, Hawkins said that if I can come up
with the $2 million, that he'd work it
so that I can make the drop.

1023
01:14:37,160 --> 01:14:39,594
- Come on, Kate--
- Now, all I can raise is
about a half a million.

1024
01:14:39,720 --> 01:14:41,836
I know you have access
to a discretionary fund.

1025
01:14:41,960 --> 01:14:43,757
Kate. Jesus, please. Listen,
you should talk to Tom about this.

1026
01:14:43,880 --> 01:14:47,111
- This isn't about Tom.
- Really.
- This is Sean.

1027
01:14:47,240 --> 01:14:49,993
I'm doin' okay.
I'm holdin' up all right.

1028
01:14:50,120 --> 01:14:51,997
Uh, Kate, l-l can't do it.
All right?

1029
01:14:52,120 --> 01:14:53,951
I--

1030
01:14:55,720 --> 01:14:58,837
He told you not to give me
any money, didn't he?

1031
01:14:58,960 --> 01:15:01,554
Kate, he's my boss. Okay?

1032
01:15:18,720 --> 01:15:20,517
Okay, eat this.

1033
01:15:22,960 --> 01:15:24,757
Thank you.

1034
01:15:33,760 --> 01:15:36,718
Again, I say if it
were my kid, I would pay.

1035
01:15:36,840 --> 01:15:39,229
I like the idea, "Yeah, you want
the money, come and get it."

1036
01:15:39,360 --> 01:15:41,999
And when he comes and gets it, I hope
somebody cuts their heads off, you know?

1037
01:15:42,120 --> 01:15:46,636
I'd get my boys from the Bronx,
and we'd just totally--

1038
01:15:46,760 --> 01:15:48,671
- Take care of him.
- We'd mess him up big time.

1039
01:15:48,800 --> 01:15:51,314
I think he's risking
his son's life.

1040
01:15:51,440 --> 01:15:53,749
I think he's a fool.
His child's life is in danger.

1041
01:15:53,880 --> 01:15:55,677
Pay the money.
Get on with your life.

1042
01:15:55,800 --> 01:15:59,588
I'd beg, borrow and steal,
if I had to. He should pay.

1043
01:15:59,720 --> 01:16:01,517
What?

1044
01:16:01,640 --> 01:16:04,871
- A man calls me at my home today.
- Mm-hmm.

1045
01:16:05,000 --> 01:16:07,958
He ask me to look in my mailbox.

1046
01:16:08,080 --> 01:16:11,436
He told me to give you this,
and nobody else.

1047
01:16:11,560 --> 01:16:15,109
He said if the police
know anything about this...

1048
01:16:15,240 --> 01:16:19,119
if Mr Mullen knows about this...

1049
01:16:19,240 --> 01:16:21,834
they'll kill Sean.

1050
01:16:21,960 --> 01:16:23,757
Okay.

1051
01:16:38,840 --> 01:16:39,795
Who is it?

1052
01:17:21,760 --> 01:17:24,149
Oh, God!

1053
01:17:25,480 --> 01:17:27,630
It's very simple.

1054
01:17:27,760 --> 01:17:31,116
I'm growing very, very tired
of this bullshit.

1055
01:17:31,240 --> 01:17:34,915
- Then could you--
- Now it's up to you.

1056
01:17:35,040 --> 01:17:38,350
Get him to take back the reward
and pay me my money...

1057
01:17:38,480 --> 01:17:42,917
or you're gonna find pieces
of your little boy all over New York.

1058
01:17:43,040 --> 01:17:46,396
I'm not gonna waste a bullet.

1059
01:17:46,520 --> 01:17:49,318
I'm just gonna sharpen my knife.

1060
01:17:51,720 --> 01:17:55,315
Oh, God! Please!

1061
01:18:07,680 --> 01:18:10,353
And he never raised
his voice at all, Kate?

1062
01:18:10,480 --> 01:18:12,755
No, he-- No, he was whispering.

1063
01:18:12,880 --> 01:18:15,474
I-- He was whispering.

1064
01:18:16,960 --> 01:18:19,269
Okay. Come on.
We'll take it to the lab.

1065
01:18:22,320 --> 01:18:26,916
You paid off
to save your airline.

1066
01:18:27,040 --> 01:18:29,679
Why won't you pay off
to save your son?

1067
01:18:40,880 --> 01:18:44,839
I'm not a marriage counsellor.
I'm here to get your boy back.

1068
01:19:06,080 --> 01:19:07,752
I'm sorry.

1069
01:19:09,400 --> 01:19:11,277
I hope...

1070
01:19:11,400 --> 01:19:13,868
that you can
forgive me for that.

1071
01:19:17,400 --> 01:19:20,517
And for what I have to do now.

1072
01:19:22,280 --> 01:19:24,430
Get the shirt to Forensics.

1073
01:19:24,560 --> 01:19:27,120
- Make sure they check for
more than one blood type.
- Sure, Lonnie.

1074
01:19:27,240 --> 01:19:31,119
Where are you goin', Tom?
Where are you goin'? What you--

1075
01:19:32,680 --> 01:19:34,477
I'm not-- All right.

1076
01:19:34,600 --> 01:19:37,672
Just think before you act.

1077
01:19:41,360 --> 01:19:43,669
- There he is.
- Mr Mullen!
- Mr Mullen!

1078
01:19:56,640 --> 01:19:58,995
- I'd like to make a statement.
- Quiet.

1079
01:19:59,120 --> 01:20:03,272
And that is that I'm undeterred
in my course of action.

1080
01:20:06,840 --> 01:20:08,751
And I'm raising the reward.

1081
01:20:08,880 --> 01:20:13,510
Uh, I'm raising it
by $2 million.

1082
01:20:13,640 --> 01:20:17,030
- Mr Mullen, why are you doing this?
- I want my son back.

1083
01:20:18,360 --> 01:20:20,590
Thank you. Thank you.

1084
01:20:20,720 --> 01:20:23,757
The FBl's efforts
in this area--

1085
01:20:30,080 --> 01:20:34,278
This just in: Tom Mullen
has reportedly raised the reward money
for his son's life...

1086
01:20:34,400 --> 01:20:37,517
by $2 million.

1087
01:20:53,960 --> 01:20:56,520
Hey.

1088
01:20:56,640 --> 01:20:58,596
Where are you goin'?

1089
01:21:09,120 --> 01:21:11,111
You've ruined my life.

1090
01:21:12,720 --> 01:21:14,392
Who the hell you think
I'm doing this for?

1091
01:21:14,680 --> 01:21:18,673
A stunning development tonight as
Tom Mullen doubles the reward money...

1092
01:21:18,800 --> 01:21:21,473
to $4 million
for the capture of--

1093
01:21:24,880 --> 01:21:27,189
- What?
- Wanna talk to your son?

1094
01:21:28,440 --> 01:21:32,035
- Yes, of course I do.
- Mmm, Daddy? Dad?

1095
01:21:32,160 --> 01:21:33,878
Sean.

1096
01:21:34,000 --> 01:21:37,709
- Sean. Sean. Son.
- Sean? I wanna listen.

1097
01:21:37,840 --> 01:21:40,400
- That's enough.
- No, put him back on.
I wanna-- I wanna talk to him.

1098
01:21:40,520 --> 01:21:42,158
You just did.

1099
01:21:42,280 --> 01:21:45,511
Now, you listen...

1100
01:21:45,640 --> 01:21:48,108
real, real good.

1101
01:21:48,240 --> 01:21:51,755
You got one more chance to pay up
or you're never gonna talk to him again.

1102
01:21:51,880 --> 01:21:54,075
No more fuckin' around.

1103
01:21:54,200 --> 01:21:56,714
This is it right now.

1104
01:21:56,840 --> 01:21:58,831
What's it gonna be?

1105
01:22:04,600 --> 01:22:08,275
No. Bullshit. You're not gonna
touch him. You can't be that stupid.

1106
01:22:08,400 --> 01:22:10,516
Do you have any idea
the rain of shit I can put on you?

1107
01:22:10,640 --> 01:22:15,156
Look at your wife.
Look at her face, motherfucker.
Do you know what I can do to your boy?

1108
01:22:15,280 --> 01:22:17,589
Is it dark where you're calling from?
You got the shades drawn?

